{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χαλκ-εῖον</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>χαλκ-ήϊον</b>, τό, =[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" {χαλκεία} 11, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.68, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 47, 77, 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.40, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 300b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ={χαλκίον} (which see): <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>cauldron, pot,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.81, 152 (variant{χαλκίον}), 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ νούσων” 4.39, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 329a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] codices: especially <b>copper</b> in baths, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 9.8 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χ. ἐρυθρόν <b>vessel</b> of pure copper, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἑλκῶν” 12; χ. μολυβοῦν “POxy.” 1648.62 (2nd c.AD). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>concave metal reflector</b> in a lamp, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 7.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>bronze structure,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Pausanias Periegeta 2.22.2. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> τὰ χαλκεῖα (i.e. ἱερά), at Athens, <b>a festival at the end of the month Pyanopsion,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Phanodemus Historicus 22, 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 90, compare 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 7.105 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; title of play by Menander.","strongNumber":"G9694","accentedUnicode":"χαλκεῖον","shortDef":"a brass cauldron","mediumDef":"a brass cauldron","stepGloss":"a brass cauldron","stepTransliteration":"chalkeion","_step_Type":"word"}]}